<usermanual>
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	

								*Social Desirability Scale (SDS)*
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	

Script Author: Katja Borchert, Ph.D. (katjab@millisecond.com) for Millisecond Software, LLC
Date: 05-04-2018
last updated:  02-28-2022 by K. Borchert (katjab@millisecond.com) for Millisecond Software, LLC

Script Copyright © 02-28-2022 Millisecond Software

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
BACKGROUND INFO 	
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
This script implements a computerized version of the Social Desirability Scale (SDS) by:

Crowne, D.P. & Marlowe, D.A. (1960). A new scale of social desirability
independent of pathology, Journal of Consulting Psychology, 24, 351.

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
OVERVIEW
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
33 true-false questions, self report
The social-desirable behavior is scored with 1 point:
true = 1, false = 0 (reversed scored questions with R: true = 0; false = 1)

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
DURATION 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
the default set-up of the script takes appr. 3 minutes to complete
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
DATA FILE INFORMATION 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
The default data stored in the data files are:

(1) Raw data file: 'sds.iqdat'

date, time:						date and time script was run with the current group/subjectnumber 
subject, group, session:	  	with the current subject/groupnumber/session id
build:							the Inquisit bui

q*_response:					response given (in assigned values: 0 (false)-1 (true)) 
								Note: questions marked with 'R' are automatically reversed scored
									
q*_latency:						how much time (in ms) the participant spent on the surveypage with this 
								particular question (the last time this particular surveypage was visited)


(2) Summary data file: 'sds_summary.iqdat' (Inquisit Lab: one data file per participant)

inquisit.version:				Inquisit version run
computer.platform:				the platform the script was run on (win/mac/ios/android)
startDate:						date script was run
startTime:						time script was started
subjectid:						assigned subject id number
groupid:						assigned group id number
sessionid:						assigned session id number
elapsedTime:					time it took to run script (in ms); measured from onset to offset of script
completed:						0 = script was not completed (prematurely aborted); 
								1 = script was completed (all conditions run)
								
SDS_score:						the total score (Range: 0 - 33)
								the higher the score, the more social-desirable behavior was reported
																
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
INSTRUCTIONS 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
see section Editable Parameters
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
EDITABLE CODE 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
check below for (relatively) easily editable parameters, stimuli, instructions etc. 
Keep in mind that you can use this script as a template and therefore always "mess" with the entire code 
to further customize your experiment.

The parameters you can change are:

/pageinstructions:			the instructions that appear at the top of each surveypage

</usermanual>


*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	EDITABLE PARAMETERS
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************

<parameters>
/pageinstructions = "Read each item and decide whether it is true or false for you. Try to work rapidly and answer each question.
"
</parameters>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	EDITABLE INSTRUCTIONS
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
<instruct>
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 3.00%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
</instruct>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
							REMAINING CODE: Customize after careful consideration only
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	DEFAULTS:
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
requires Inquisit 6.5.2.0

<defaults>
/minimumversion = "6.5.2.0"
/canvasaspectratio = (4,3)
</defaults>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	DATA: this section contains data file information
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************

********************
Summary data
********************

<summarydata>
/ columns = (inquisit.version, computer.platform, script.startDate, script.startTime, script.subjectId, script.groupId, script.sessionId, script.elapsedTime, 
script.completed,
expressions.SDS_score)
</summarydata>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	VALUES: automatically updated
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************


*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	EXPRESSIONS
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************

<expressions>
/SDS_score = radiobuttons.q1.response + radiobuttons.q2.response + radiobuttons.q3R.response + radiobuttons.q4.response +
radiobuttons.q5R.response + radiobuttons.q6R.response + radiobuttons.q7.response + radiobuttons.q8.response +
radiobuttons.q9R.response + radiobuttons.q10R.response + radiobuttons.q11R.response + radiobuttons.q12R.response + 
radiobuttons.q13.response + radiobuttons.q14R.response + radiobuttons.q15R.response + radiobuttons.q16.response +
radiobuttons.q17.response + radiobuttons.q18.response + radiobuttons.q19R.response + radiobuttons.q20.response +
radiobuttons.q21.response + radiobuttons.q22R.response + radiobuttons.q23R.response + radiobuttons.q24.response +
radiobuttons.q25.response + radiobuttons.q26.response + radiobuttons.q27.response + radiobuttons.q28R.response +
radiobuttons.q29.response + radiobuttons.q30R.response + radiobuttons.q31.response + radiobuttons.q32R.response +
radiobuttons.q33.response
</expressions>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	QUESTIONS
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
Note: by default all questions are required to be answered. To change
/required = false

<radiobuttons q1>
/caption = "Before voting I thoroughly investigate the qualifications of all the candidates."
/ options = ("True ", "False ")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q2>
/caption = "I never hesitate to go out of my way to help someone in trouble."
/ options = ("True ", "False ")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q3R>
/caption = "It is sometimes hard for me to go on with my work if I am not encouraged."
/ options = ("True ", "False ")
/ optionvalues = ("0", "1")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q4>
/caption = "I have never intensely disliked anyone."
/ options = ("True ", "False ")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q5R>
/caption = "On occasions I have had doubts about my ability to succeed in life."
/ options = ("True ", "False ")
/ optionvalues = ("0", "1")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q6R>
/caption = "I sometimes feel resentful when I don’t get my way."
/ options = ("True ", "False ")
/ optionvalues = ("0", "1")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q7>
/caption = "I am always careful about my manner of dress."
/ options = ("True ", "False ")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q8>
/caption = "My table manners at home are as good as when I eat out in a restaurant."
/ options = ("True ", "False ")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q9R>
/caption = "If I could get into a movie without paying and be sure I was not seen, I would probably do it."
/ options = ("True ", "False ")
/ optionvalues = ("0", "1")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q10R>
/caption = "On a few occasions, I have given up something because I thought too little of my ability."
/ options = ("True ", "False ")
/ optionvalues = ("0", "1")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q11R>
/caption = "I like to gossip at times."
/ options = ("True ", "False ")
/ optionvalues = ("0", "1")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q12R>
/caption = "There have been times when I felt like rebelling against people in authority even though I knew they were right."
/ options = ("True ", "False ")
/ optionvalues = ("0", "1")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q13>
/caption = "No matter who I’m talking to, I’m always a good listener."
/ options = ("True ", "False ")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q14R>
/caption = "I can remember “playing sick” to get out of something."
/ options = ("True ", "False ")
/ optionvalues = ("0", "1")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q15R>
/caption = "There have been occasions when I have taken advantage of someone."
/ options = ("True ", "False ")
/ optionvalues = ("0", "1")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q16>
/caption = "I’m always willing to admit it when I make a mistake."
/ options = ("True ", "False ")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q17>
/caption = "I always try to practice what I preach."
/ options = ("True ", "False ")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q18>
/caption = "I don’t find it particularly difficult to get along with loudmouthed, obnoxious people"
/ options = ("True ", "False ")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q19R>
/caption = "I sometimes try to get even rather than forgive and forget."
/ options = ("True ", "False ")
/ optionvalues = ("0", "1")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q20>
/caption = "When I don’t know something I don’t mind at all admitting it."
/ options = ("True ", "False ")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q21>
/caption = "I am always courteous, even to people who are disagreeable."
/ options = ("True ", "False ")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q22R>
/caption = "At times I have really insisted on having things my own way."
/ options = ("True ", "False ")
/ optionvalues = ("0", "1")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q23R>
/caption = "There have been occasions when I felt like smashing things."
/ options = ("True ", "False ")
/ optionvalues = ("0", "1")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q24>
/caption = "I would never think of letting someone else be punished for my wrong-doings."
/ options = ("True ", "False ")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q25>
/caption = "I never resent being asked to return a favor."
/ options = ("True ", "False ")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q26>
/caption = "I have never been irked when people expressed ideas very different from my own"
/ options = ("True ", "False ")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q27>
/caption = "I never make a long trip without checking the safety of my car."
/ options = ("True ", "False ")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q28R>
/caption = "There have been times when I was quite jealous of the good fortune of others."
/ options = ("True ", "False ")
/ optionvalues = ("0", "1")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q29>
/caption = "I have almost never felt the urge to tell someone off."
/ options = ("True ", "False ")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q30R>
/caption = "I am sometimes irritated by people who ask favors of me."
/ options = ("True ", "False ")
/ optionvalues = ("0", "1")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q31>
/caption = "I have never felt that I was punished without cause."
/ options = ("True ", "False ")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q32R>
/caption = "I sometimes think when people have a misfortune they only got what they deserved."
/ options = ("True ", "False ")
/ optionvalues = ("0", "1")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q33>
/caption = "I have never deliberately said something that hurt someone’s feelings."
/ options = ("True ", "False ")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontal
</radiobuttons>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	SURVEYPAGES
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************

<surveypage SDS1>
/ caption ="<%parameters.pageinstructions%>"
/ questions = [1 = q1, q2, q3R, q4]
</surveypage>

<surveypage SDS2>
/ caption ="<%parameters.pageinstructions%>"
/ questions = [1 = q5R, q6R, q7, q8]
</surveypage>

<surveypage SDS3>
/ caption ="<%parameters.pageinstructions%>"
/ questions = [1 = q9R, q10R, q11R, q12R]
</surveypage>

<surveypage SDS4>
/ caption ="<%parameters.pageinstructions%>"
/ questions = [1 = q13, q14R, q15R, q16]
</surveypage>

<surveypage SDS5>
/ caption ="<%parameters.pageinstructions%>"
/ questions = [1= q17, q18, q19R, q20]
</surveypage>

<surveypage SDS6>
/ caption ="<%parameters.pageinstructions%>"
/ questions = [1 = q21, q22R, q23R, q24]
</surveypage>

<surveypage SDS7>
/ caption ="<%parameters.pageinstructions%>"
/ questions = [1 = q25, q26, q27, q28R]
</surveypage>

<surveypage SDS8>
/ caption ="<%parameters.pageinstructions%>"
/ questions = [1= q29, q30R, q31, q32R]
</surveypage>

<surveypage SDS9>
/ caption ="<%parameters.pageinstructions%>"
/ questions = [1 = q33]
</surveypage>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	SURVEY
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
Notes:
- presents the surveypages
- to take pictures of each screen set /screencapture = true

<survey SDS>
/pages = [
	1 = SDS1;
	2 = SDS2;
	3 = SDS3;
	4 = SDS4;
	5 = SDS5;
	6 = SDS6;
	7 = SDS7;
	8 = SDS8;
	9 = SDS9;
]
/screencapture = false
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 3%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ subcaptionfontstyle = ("Arial", 1.5%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ itemfontstyle = ("Arial", 3%, true, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ responsefontstyle = ("Arial", 2.5%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ txcolor = (0, 0, 0)
/ showpagenumbers = false
/ showquestionnumbers = true
/ navigationbuttonfontstyle = ("Arial", 3%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ navigationbuttonsize = (15%, 5%)
/ backbuttonposition = (20%, 90%)
/ nextbuttonposition = (70%, 90%)
/ finishlabel = "Finish"
</survey>

